<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Kolina on 04-24-2001 02:11 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Ok, unless you are very familiar with the Cleric Epic, you need not read this, but if you are....here goes.

Ok, my best friend is a lvl 58 cleric.  We completed every step of the cleric epic up until the Zordak Ragefire.   We killed Ragefire, and when the dragon spawned, we threw everything at him we had....and failed  :(.   We had him down to the Z in his name when the last tank died, and the castors just kept getting summoned and killed (some died as many as 10 times in the attempt.)

Here's my question....is there ANYthing we can do to short circuit the quest without having to start over at step one.   We still have the Orb of Frozen Water and the Orb of Clear Water, and simply need that last orb, but every step of the cleric epic seems to depend on the step before it.   All we actually need is the Message to Natasha to turn into Natasha to get the Shimmering Pearl which will cause the dragon to spawn.  We need Lord Gimblox Signet Ring (which we have) to turn in to get the 2nd Ornate Sea Shell to turn in to get the message.  Now my question is, has anyone ever encountered this before?  Natasha Whitewater is involved in the quest in 3 different places.   Is it possible to turn in something meant for the 3rd Natasha to the first Natasha that resides in Lake Rathe, or does it have to be the proper Natasha spawned in the proper way?  I'm assuming that it does, but am not sure.   We tried to piggyback with another cleric last night and it didn't work.  He had the plasmatic priest robe to turn in, which spawned the Natasha that we needed.   We were hoping beyond hope that once he spawned and used that Natasha, she would stay around long enough for my friend to also turn in her ring, but Natasha poofed as soon as the first cleric turned in his ring and got his sea shell II.

ANY ideas would be extremely helpful.   Can you imagine having to do your entire epic twice?!   We are ready to start over, but this is my last ditch effort to see if anyone else has encountered this and found a way around it.

Thanks</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
